-- Thai stocks fall after blast at anti-government protest
-- By Viparat Jantraprap
-- Fri Jan 17, 2014 02:43AM EST
-- None



BANGKOK, Jan 17 (Reuters) - Thai stocks fell on Friday after a bomb went off as anti-government protesters marched in central Bangkok, spurring fears about rising political tension.

By 0735 GMT, the benchmark SET index <.SETI> was down 0.7 percent at 1,292.38, having lost around 1 percent at one point. The index moved narrowly in the morning session and was nearly flat by the midday trading break at 0530 GMT.